  "prompt": "How hard is it to be a teacher?",
  "response": "Being a teacher can be challenging in several ways:\n\n1. Workload\n- Long hours beyond classroom time\n- Lesson planning\n- Grading assignments\n- Administrative tasks\n\n2. Emotional challenges\n- Managing student behavior\n- Supporting students with personal difficulties\n- Dealing with diverse learning needs\n- Maintaining student engagement\n\n3. Professional challenges\n- Low pay in many regions\n- Limited resources\n- Constant curriculum changes\n- High-stakes testing pressures\n\n4. Personal skills required\n- Patience\n- Adaptability\n- Strong communication\n- Emotional intelligence\n- Content knowledge\n- Classroom management skills\n\n5. Potential stress factors\n- Large class sizes\n- Bureaucratic requirements\n- Parent interactions\n- Performance evaluations\n\n6. Positive aspects\n- Rewarding work\n- Making a difference in students' lives\n- Continuous learning\n- Job stability\n- Summer breaks\n\nDifficulty varies by:\n- Grade level\n- Subject area\n- School environment\n- Individual teaching style\n- Personal resilience\n\nOverall, teaching is demanding but can be very fulfilling for those passionate about education.",
